    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis was originally reported here, so see that for the full context\r\n* https://github.com/neovide/neovide/issues/2140\r\n\r\nLoading session files can cause Neovim to send a `grid_cursor_goto` event with negative coordinates like -57, 19 in the log given. This only happens with Neovim nightly and not with Neovim 0.9.4.  The terminal mode Neovim is also fine\r\n\r\nNote, I did quickly try to create a failing test, but it was harder than I though because apparently it requires the window layout to be changed while the cursor is at the command line, which does not happen when running `helpers.source`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a .vim file containing the following minimised script:\r\n```vim\r\nset shortmess=A\r\ntabnew +setlocal\\ bufhidden=wipe\r\nresize 1\r\ntabnext\r\nedit newfile.txt\r\n```\r\n2. Run neovide --multigrid -- --clean\r\n3. `:so` the script\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should send valid coordinates\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1623+g8c6b0a5f2, Neovide 0.11.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty/Neovide\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nManually built",
